  "body": "# Problem\r\n`Block screenshots` and `hiding preview` on app switching works differently on iOS vs Android. This issue is to update the copy for iOS to accurately reflect the behavior.\r\n\r\n### Current\r\n`Block screenshots`\r\n### Expected\r\n`Hide preview`\r\n\r\n##Background\r\niOS hides the preview while allowing screenshots, whereas Android has a single function that hides preview and blocks screenshots.\r\n\r\n'How do I allow making screenshots?' is a frequently asked question, we wanted to make this setting easier to discover by referring to the requested feature 'Block screenshots', considering hiding previews as a side effect. This has already been implemented, but currently appears on iOS as well.\r\n\r\nBecause on iOS the function does not actually Block screenshots but hides preview only, we want to use `Hide preview` on iOS.\r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\nAndroid setting uses label `Block screenshots`\r\niOS setting uses label `Hide preview`\r\n\r\n",
